<section class="whymatters section section--alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="whymatters__header">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Why Memory Matters</span>
      <h2 class="section__title">Stop Re-Explaining <span class="highlight">Yourself</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="whymatters__grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Context compounds</h3>
        <p>Every conversation adds to what your AI knows about you — your preferences, your projects, your open loops. A month in, it's not answering from scratch anymore.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Fewer repeated instructions</h3>
        <p>Tell it once how you like summaries formatted, which timezone you're in, or how you write emails — it applies that everywhere, not just in the thread you said it in.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Automation needs memory</h3>
        <p>Scheduling, triage, and reminders only work well if the AI remembers what happened last time. Memory is what turns a chatbot into something that can actually act on your behalf.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

